      "description": "One difference I noticed is that the `int` parameters have changed from a simple `integer` with a `int32` format to this hybrid string/integer format with a regex...\r\n\r\nThe reason?\r\n\r\nIn ASP.NET Core, reading numbers from JSON is set to `JsonSerializerOptions.NumberHandling.AllowReadingFromString`, which means that our server would allow both strings and int, so this is done.\r\n\r\nYou can change that to `Strict` if you want to return back to Integer"
